        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42441",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ceefour",
                        "name": "ceefour",
                        "displayName": "Hendy Irawan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This issue still exists in ZF 1.10.8 and even on trunk today.\r\n\r\nMaintainers, please commit this patch.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ceefour",
                        "name": "ceefour",
                        "displayName": "Hendy Irawan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-10-07T05:29:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-10-07T05:29:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42773",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=far-blue",
                        "name": "far-blue",
                        "displayName": "Robert Goldsmith",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This issue actually also exists in the 1.11 RC1 release. The effective result of this bug is that it is not possible to register multiple autoloaders with either the same namespace or namespaces with the same starting string (e.g. 'account' and 'accountAdmin').\r\n\r\nthe patch supplied for the fix, however, is slightly incorrect in that it does not remove the break on line 342 so the foreach on line 335 doesn't loop and fill additional autoloaders into the array.\r\n\r\nadditional patch:\r\n{noformat}\r\n--- Autoloader.php      2010-07-12 14:13:33.000000000 +0700\r\n+++ Autoloader.new.php  2010-07-12 14:14:12.000000000 +0700\r\n@@ -338,7 +338,7 @@\r\n             }\r\n             if (0 === strpos($class, $ns)) {\r\n                 $namespace   = $ns;\r\n                $autoloaders = array_merge($autoloaders, $this->getNamespaceAutoloaders($ns));\r\n -                break;\r\n             }\r\n         }\r\n{noformat}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=far-blue",
                        "name": "far-blue",
                        "displayName": "Robert Goldsmith",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-10-29T08:57:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-10-29T08:57:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43472",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wadim.grasza",
                        "name": "wadim.grasza",
                        "displayName": "Wadim Grasza",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "That's not all.\r\n\r\nThe effective result of this bug is also that you cannot chain an autoloader for an empty namespace.\r\n\r\nTo reproduce:\r\n1. Register 'My_' namespace with the autoloader.\r\n2. Invoke pushAutoloader for an empty namespace.\r\n3. Try to autoload a class that starts with 'My_'.\r\n\r\nResult:\r\nThe autoloader pushed in 2. is not added to the list of tried autoloaders.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wadim.grasza",
                        "name": "wadim.grasza",
                        "displayName": "Wadim Grasza",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-05T10:24:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-05T10:24:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44251",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=arondeparon",
                        "name": "arondeparon",
                        "displayName": "Aron Rotteveel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This bug still exists in 1.11.2. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=arondeparon",
                        "name": "arondeparon",
                        "displayName": "Aron Rotteveel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-02-03T02:45:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-02-03T02:45:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46004",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Exists a problem with array_merge and numeric indexes see:\nhttp:\/\/pastebin.com\/0CHBYRSj, by this that this solution work fine.\n\nAttach a patch with tests.\n\nGreetings\nRamon",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
